#. <section class="sutta" id="an8.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.38:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.38:0.2"
msgid "4. Dānavagga"
msgstr "4. Giving"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an8.38:0.3"
msgid "38. Sappurisasutta"
msgstr "38. A Good Person"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an8.38:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Sappuriso, bhikkhave, kule jāyamāno bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya "
"hoti—"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a good person is born in a family for the benefit, welfare, and "
"happiness of the people."

msgctxt "an8.38:1.2"
msgid ""
"mātāpitūnaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti, puttadārassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya "
"hoti, dāsakammakaraporisassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti, mittāmaccānaṃ "
"atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti, pubbapetānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti, rañño "
"atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti, devatānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti, "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti."
msgstr ""
"For the benefit, welfare, and happiness of mother and father; children and "
"partners; bondservants, workers, and staff; friends and colleagues; departed "
"ancestors; the king; the deities; and ascetics and brahmins."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.245"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: hitāya sukhāya → hitāya …pe… (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an8.38:2.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāmegho sabbasassāni sampādento bahuno janassa "
"atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like a great rain cloud, which nourishes all the crops for the benefit, "
"welfare, and happiness of the people."

msgctxt "an8.38:2.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sappuriso kule jāyamāno bahuno janassa atthāya "
"hitāya sukhāya hoti—"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a good person is born in a family for the benefit, welfare, "
"and happiness of the people. …"

msgctxt "an8.38:2.3"
msgid ""
"mātāpitūnaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti, puttadārassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya "
"hoti, dāsakammakaraporisassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti, mittāmaccānaṃ "
"atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti, pubbapetānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti, rañño "
"atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti, devatānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti, "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hotīti."
msgstr ""

# See BB’s note for dividing these verses. I have adjusted the markup accordingly.
#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: Bahūnaṃ → bahunnaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.38:3.1"
msgid "Bahūnaṃ vata atthāya,"
msgstr "A wise person living at home"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.38:3.2"
msgid "sappañño gharamāvasaṃ;"
msgstr "benefits many people."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.38:3.3"
msgid "Mātaraṃ pitaraṃ pubbe,"
msgstr "Neither by day or at night do they neglect"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.38:3.4"
msgid "rattindivamatandito."
msgstr "their mother, father, and ancestors."

#. <br>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an8.38:4.1"
msgid "Pūjeti sahadhammena,"
msgstr "They venerate them in accord with the teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.38:4.2"
msgid "pubbekatamanussaraṃ;"
msgstr "remembering what they have done."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.38:4.3"
msgid "Anāgāre pabbajite,"
msgstr "One of settled faith and good nature"

#. <br>
#. VAR: brahmacārayo → brahmacārino (s1-3)
msgctxt "an8.38:4.4"
msgid "apace brahmacārayo."
msgstr "venerates the homeless renunciates,"

#. <br>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an8.38:5.1"
msgid "Niviṭṭhasaddho pūjeti,"
msgstr "the mendicant spiritual practitioners,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: dhamme ca pesalo → dhammedhapesale (bj) | dhamme ca pesale (mr)
msgctxt "an8.38:5.2"
msgid "ñatvā dhamme ca pesalo;"
msgstr "knowing their good-hearted qualities."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.38:5.3"
msgid "Rañño hito devahito,"
msgstr "Good for the king, good for the gods,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.38:5.4"
msgid "ñātīnaṃ sakhinaṃ hito."
msgstr "and good for relatives and friends."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: Sabbesaṃ → sabbesu (mr)
#. VAR: so → sa (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an8.38:6.1"
msgid "Sabbesaṃ so hito hoti,"
msgstr "In fact, they’re good for everyone,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.38:6.2"
msgid "saddhamme suppatiṭṭhito;"
msgstr "well grounded in the true teaching."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.38:6.3"
msgid "Vineyya maccheramalaṃ,"
msgstr "Rid of the stain of stinginess,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.38:6.4"
msgid "sa lokaṃ bhajate sivan”ti."
msgstr "they’ll enjoy a world of grace.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.38:6.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
